-- Arsenal, Tottenham Eye U.S. Striker Dempsey, Sun Says: Roundup
-- B y   A l e x   D u f f
-- 2012-04-09T09:51:30Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-04-09/arsenal-tottenham-eye-u-s-striker-dempsey-sun-says-roundup.html
The following is a roundup of soccer
stories from U.K. newspapers, with clickable links to the Web.  Dempsey Talks  Clint Dempsey , who has 21 goals for Fulham this season, is
talking to the team about his future amid interest from Arsenal
and Tottenham,  the Sun  reported.  Dempsey said he’ll make a decision after the end of the
season, according to the Sun, which put his transfer market
value at 10 million pounds ($15.9 million).  Saints Offer  Southampton will offer Wolves 4 million pounds to sign
striker  Kevin Doyle , the  Daily Mirror  reported.  Reading is also interested in resigning 28-year-old Doyle,
the Mirror said. Southampton leads the second-tier Championship
and Reading is in second place.  Arsenal Exit  Per Mertesacker may leave Arsenal after one season, the
 Daily Mirror  reported.  The German defender, who the Gunners signed for 10 million
pounds, is sidelined with an ankle injury and could be traded in
the off-season, according to the Mirror.  Crouch Acclaim  Stoke coach  Tony Pulis  says striker  Peter Crouch  deserves a
place in England’s European Championship squad,  the Independent 
reported.  Stoke hasn’t had a player called up to the national team
since Mark Chamberlain in 1984, the newspaper said.  To contact the reporters on this story:
